 Introduction
Fashion plays an important role in personal appearance and confidence. However, choosing the right outfit every day can be time-consuming and confusing, especially when considering matching clothes, accessories, and budget constraints. Many users struggle to decide what to wear based on their existing wardrobe and available options.
With the rapid advancement in Artificial Intelligence (AI), Deep Learning, and Computer Vision, it is now possible to develop intelligent systems that can assist users in making better fashion decisions. The Smart Me Fashion Assistant is designed to analyze clothing images and provide personalized outfit recommendations.
This system helps users by suggesting matching outfits, shoes, and accessories while also considering their budget. It simplifies the decision-making process and enhances the overall user experience.

 Objectives
•	To develop an AI-based fashion recommendation system 
•	To identify clothing items using image processing 
•	To suggest matching outfits, shoes, and accessories 
•	To provide budget-friendly recommendations 
•	To enhance user experience through personalization 
•	To automate daily outfit selection 

 Problem Statement
Many individuals face difficulty in selecting appropriate outfits daily due to lack of fashion knowledge, time constraints, and budget limitations. Existing solutions do not provide personalized and budget-aware recommendations based on user-uploaded images. Therefore, there is a need for an intelligent system that can analyze clothing items and suggest suitable combinations efficiently.

 Proposed System
The proposed system is an AI-powered Smart Me Fashion Assistant that uses Deep Learning and Computer Vision techniques to analyze clothing images uploaded by users. The system identifies different clothing items and generates recommendations for matching outfits.
It also integrates budget constraints to suggest affordable options for completing the look, including shoes and accessories. The system can be accessed through a web or mobile interface.

 Methodology
1.	Data collection (fashion datasets, clothing images) 
2.	Image preprocessing and labeling 
3.	Model training using Deep Learning techniques 
4.	Clothing item detection using Computer Vision 
5.	Recommendation engine development 
6.	Budget filtering and suggestion system 
7.	Testing and deployment 

